{"word":"Goshen","slug":"goshen","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Goshen</b> <a href=\"#/H1657\">H1657</a> <br/> 1. A district in Egypt especially adapted to herds and flocks<br/> - Israelites dwelt in<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=45&verse=10'>Gen 45:10</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=46&verse=28'>Gen 46:28</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=47'>Gen 47</a> <br/> - Exempted from plagues<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=2&chapter=8&verse=22'>Exo 8:22</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=2&chapter=9&verse=26'>Exo 9:26</a> <br/> 2. A town and district of Judah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=10&verse=41'>Jos 10:41</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=11&verse=16'>Jos 11:16</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=15&verse=51'>Jos 15:51</a>"}]}